title: "C# Language Practices"
description: "Standards for clear, safe C# code"
tags: [csharp, language]
---

## Naming and Structure
- PascalCase for methods; camelCase for fields and locals; _camelCase for private fields.
- Small, cohesive classes; single responsibility.

## Nullability and Errors
- Enable nullable reference types; avoid `!` suppression.
- Use guard clauses and specific exceptions.

## Async
- Use async/await; configure awaits carefully (`ConfigureAwait(false)` in libraries).

## Collections and LINQ
- Prefer explicit types over `var` when clarity improves.
- Avoid multiple enumerations; materialize when needed.

## Testing and DI
- Constructor injection for dependencies.
- Favor interfaces; avoid static singletons.

## Validation Checklist
- [ ] Nullable enabled; null-handling explicit
- [ ] Exceptions meaningful and actionable
- [ ] DI used; no hidden static state
- [ ] Tests cover logic paths

